10:
Yeah, nope. I don't understand this
at all!
13:
Why does every witch and warlock
have to be so cryptic in their
writing?! Would it kill them to write in
plain text for once?
17: Is it that difficult to understand?
22:
Totally! I mean, you'd have to be
some kind of super nerd—
25:
Er, I mean, uh... Stella! How long have
you been here, dearie?
27:
S-something like this is mere child's
play for a witch of the world such as
myself!
34:
This one here's a Catfolk book.
"Cursebreaking: Where to Begin?"
38:
E-even a master of the arcane arts
needs to return to the basics every
now and then, right?
42:
I wondered why you were up so late,
but it turns out you were just
studying...
45: I'll put on some tea. Want some?
53:
So you took interest in other worlds
because you wanted to deepen
your understanding of magic?
56:
Wh-why, yes, of course! I suppose
that's one way you could put it.
59:
Well, that's good. It was pretty hard
to get Light out of that ice cube last
week...
63:
Oh, well, uh... the past is in the past,
right?
68:
Did these books not exist in the
Endless Blue?
72:
I thought I'd be able to obtain higher
knowledge from other worlds.
75:
You see, there's a very specific type
of magic I'm hoping to get a better
understanding of.
77:
I suppose it was my fault for not
telling you in the first place.
81:
Allow me to show you myself. Come
with me for a field trip?
90: You'd do well to bundle up.
97: This is Rei. She's my twin sister.
99:
We've always been together. The
world wasn't always kind to us, but
at as long as we had each other, we
were okay.
101:
But one day... she fell ill from a fatal
disease.
105: So you mean to say that you—
109:
Yes. It was I who stopped time for
her.
111:
I still haven't found a way to free her
from this spell. I'm so close... but I
need more time.
113:
I've imprisoned her in a cage frozen
in time.
119:
Beautiful, just beautiful. Totes got
the waterworks going that time,
didn't ya?
125:
Sorry, friends. She can be SUCH a
drama queen sometimes.
128:
Alk, it seems that Rei is
communicating with us somehow.
134:
She IS a magical genius such as
myself, after all. Even when frozen in
time, she can still communicate
telepathically.
137:
Sup. You can call me Rei or
whatever, I guess.
143:
And that's how I ended up traveling
with these fine people.
145:
For REALS?! Other worlds? That's, like,
totes outta this world—literally!
146:
So, like, you find any hotties yet?
Gimme the dish, Ciph!
149:
Ah, yes. Many things of beauty
indeed... If only I could show you
myself.
151:
Are you STILL playing the tragic
heroine role? Sorry, friendos. Bet
you're all tired of her theatrics,
aren'tcha?
152:
She wasn't always like this, you
know. In fact, back then—
155:
I'm gonna have to stop you right
there.
157:
You wouldn't BELIEVE how she used
to talk before this—
161:
Ahem! I BELIEVE we're all well
acquainted enough for one day. We
really must get going.
166:
But I WILL find the cure for you one
day. Just wait a little longer, dear
sister.
169:
"Dear sister?" Yikes. On second
thought, just end me already.
172:
Sorry, friendos. Don't worry about
little old me, okay?
176:
I can't believe that dummy had to
be such a downer and bring you all
here.
178:
I'm fine, really! She'd honestly be
better off forgetting about me, you
know—
185:
She's still getting a grasp of the
basics right now, it seems, so it may
take some time.
188: So don't worry about her too.
192: Did Rei say anything to you guys?
196:
Uh... "It's totes unfair that you're livin'
up your hot girl summer while I'm
stuck here, so get your butt in gear
and save me already!" Or
something like that.
200:
Heh... Is that so? I'll have to
double—no, triple my efforts then!
204: Thanks for coming along, you two.
